# Runbook: Installing VirtualBox

## Overview
This runbook outlines the steps required to install **Oracle VM VirtualBox** on a Windows host system for use in the Virtual Enterprise Network lab environment. VirtualBox provides the virtualization platform on which all virtual machines (VMs) will run.

---

## Prerequisites

### System Requirements
- **Operating System:** Windows 10/11, macOS, or Linux
- **CPU:** 64-bit processor with virtualization extensions (Intel VT-x or AMD-V)
- **RAM:** Minimum 8 GB (16 GB recommended)
- **Storage:** At least 30 GB free space
- **Administrator Privileges** required for installation

## Procedure

### Step 1: Download VirtualBox
1. Go to [https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads](https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads) (https://github.com/brennanjgriffin-svg/Virtual-Enterprise-Network/blob/main/docs/images/operations/runbooks/Core-Infrastructure/Installing-VirtualBox/Screenshot%20(200).png)
2. Choose the installer for your OS:
   - **Windows hosts:** `VirtualBox-x.x.x-Win.exe`  (Screenshot of mouse over download button)

### Step 2: Install VirtualBox 
1. Run the installer as Administrator. (Screenshot of )
2. Keep default options (networking, USB, etc.). (Screenshot of )
3. Approve driver installation prompts. (Screenshot of )
4. Click **Install** and then **Finish**. (Screenshot of install button) (Screenshot of finish)

### Step 3: Verify Install
1. Navigate to [C:\Program Files\Oracle\VirtualBox]
2. Find and launch VirtualBox application
3. **Expected Result:** VirtualBox GUI opens without error.

